result.execSummary:
The defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Pay restitution to Eduardo B. in the amount of $500.00; then pay $1,431.43 to the City of Milwaukee; then $6,723.36 to Progressive Insurance Company; then pay all applicable costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Should defendant get revoked, Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would then be paid while on Extended Supervision.    Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.
Obtain high school diploma, HSED or GED. Seek and maintain employment. Be given job and vocational training.

No contact with Eduardo B. or Sebastian H.

Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  
Cognitive thinking intervention counseling. Parenting classes/counseling.

AODA assessment and treatment. Urine screens.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Danielle L. Shelton in court, defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez not in court, in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel withdrew her bail motion and requested a plea and sentencing date.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 21, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Danielle L. Shelton in court, defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez not in court, in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel in a lengthy motion hearing in Branch 17.  Case continued to 3/02/15 at 1:30 p.m. for bail hearing and scheduling conference.

Attorney Danielle L. Shelton in court by telephone, defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez not in court, in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defense counsel requested another scheduling date (defendant was charged in 15CF623 and is before preliminary hearing court today).  File retained in court.  Scheduling conference scheduled for February 26, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Notice of Motion and Motion for Review and Modification of Bail filed by Atty. Danielle L. Shelton.

Defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Moroney, Branch 20.  Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty. Court ordered case adjourned for Scheduling Conference in Branch 20.  Scheduling conference scheduled for February 17, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with EDUARDO S.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
No driving without a valid license or insurance.

Defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge MORONEY, Branch 20.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for February 5, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
